article.headline: New Hampshire 56, Dartmouth 43
article.story: MANCHESTER, N.H. (AP) -- Marcus Bullock scored all of his 15 points on 3-pointers to lead New Hampshire to a 56-43 win over Dartmouth on Sunday. Bullock, who set the school record for career 3-pointers with his 198th early in the game, hit five of eight from beyond the arc. Shejdie Childs added 14 points for New Hampshire (3-4). Michael Lang scored 15 points for Dartmouth (1-5). New Hampshire took a 25-24 at halftime after Ioannis Karalis and Bullock hit 3-pointers. The Wildcats expanded the lead by scoring the first eight points in the second half with Bullock capping the run with another three. New Hampshire opened a 40-29 lead with 10:40 to go. The Big Green cut the Wildcat advantage to six on a Michael Lang basket with 4:38 left but couldn't get any closer. The Wildcats sealed the win at the line, making six free throws in the final 54 seconds.<
